:scan_function{trait} or :scan_function{trait1 + trait2/trait3}  -> value
  Run specified function on ALL orgs to trait to produce value.
  Example: :max{fitness} or :mean{metabolic_rate / gestation_cost}

@find_function{trait}
  Find organism with function and based on trait.
  Example: @max{fitness}

|{filter expression}
  Produce an organism set with only those organism that produce a positive trait expression
  Example:
    var dom_org = @mode{genotype_id}
    var dom_set = |{fitness >= $dom_org.fitness}

Precede either of the above with an organism set to run on only those.

$variable          -> Current value of a variable

org.trait          -> trait value for the given organism


trait:scan_function     -> Run specified function on ALL orgs to trait to produce value.
  Example: fitness:max or generation:mean

variables can be double, strings, organisms, or organism sets





